verses.verse: To the chief <S%H5329><s%> Musician <S%H5329><s%> on Neginoth, <S%H5058><s%> A Psalm <S%H4210><s%> or Song. <S%H7892><s%> God <S%H430><s%> be merciful <S%H2603><s%> to us, and bless <S%H1288><s%> us; and cause his face <S%H6440><s%> to shine <S%H215><s%> on us; Selah. <S%H5542><s%>
That your way <S%H1870><s%> may be known <S%H3045><s%> on earth, <S%H776><s%> your saving <S%H3444><s%> health <S%H3444><s%> among all <S%H3605><s%> nations. <S%H1471><s%>
Let the people <S%H5971><s%> praise <S%H3034><s%> you, O God; <S%H430><s%> let all <S%H3605><s%> the people <S%H5971><s%> praise <S%H3034><s%> you.

O let the nations <S%H3816><s%> be glad <S%H8056><s%> and sing <S%H7442><s%> for joy: for you shall judge <S%H8199><s%> the people <S%H5971><s%> righteously, <S%H4334><s%> and govern <S%H5148><s%> the nations <S%H3816><s%> on earth. <S%H776><s%> Selah. <S%H5542><s%>
Let the people <S%H5971><s%> praise <S%H3034><s%> you, O God; <S%H430><s%> let all <S%H3605><s%> the people <S%H5971><s%> praise <S%H3034><s%> you.
Then shall the earth <S%H776><s%> yield <S%H5414><s%> her increase; <S%H2981><s%> and God, <S%H430><s%> even our own God, <S%H430><s%> shall bless <S%H1288><s%> us.
God <S%H430><s%> shall bless <S%H1288><s%> us; and all <S%H3605><s%> the ends <S%H657><s%> of the earth <S%H776><s%> shall fear <S%H3372><s%> him.
